news.title: Centre releases Rs 1,671 crore to Uttar Pradesh under PMAY-Rural
news.para: A senior official said that deputy CM Keshav Maurya had written to the Centre suggesting construction of 862767 houses under PMAY-R. So far, about 26 lakh houses have been built in Uttar Pradesh under the scheme.

news.title: Gujarat housing board house owners liable for jantri-linked penalties
news.para: The issue shows that GRUD Act 2022 ignores GHB home owners who want to regularize their illegal extensions . Such property owners seeking regularization of illegal construction will not be entertained.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board notifies need-based changes for dwelling units
news.para: More than 4.5 lakh city residents living in the CHB allotted houses are likely to benefit from the relaxations, which have come into effect after the notification.

news.title: Single-window system for self-redevelopment projects in Maharashtra
news.para: Of the around 1.20 lakh registered cooperative societies and over 80,000 apartments, nearly 60,000 units are over 30 years old and likely to go for redevelopment.

news.title: Panchsheel Greens 2 residents lock society gate over water crisis in Greater Noida
news.para: After facing water disruption from January 1, the residents complained to the Greater Noida Authority, following which a team came to the society to check the pump house. They blamed it on the internal pipeline of the society.

news.title: Gurugram civic body will verify properties again after errors in IDs
news.para: Last year’s survey had concluded that 5.14 lakh properties in areas under MCG’s jurisdiction should be taxed, an increase from the 3.7 lakh on paper till then. Residents alleged that this survey was flawed, with several errors in the property IDs.

news.title: Licensed surveyors and architects to approve G+3 buildings in Kolkata
news.para: KMC officials said architects and LBS will now be able to sanction plans of four-storied buildings (G+3) not exceeding 41ft and with floor area not exceeding 5,382sqft.

news.title: HDIL promoter, dad caused Rs 6,000 crore loss to PMC bank, so no bail: Sessions court
news.para: The court said the structure and foundation of PMC bank collapsed and was disturbed. It was observed that with this all depositors and account holders have suffered unbearable, financial, mental pain, agony and the same is also required to be considered sensitively.

news.title: Summons to Supertech, MD over alleged forgery, criminal breach of trust
news.para: Gaurav Vij had alleged in his complaint that he had given money to the company through its representatives for short term investment in September 2012.

news.title: Sonam Kapoor sells apartment in Mumbai's BKC for Rs 32.50 crore
news.para: She had purchased this apartment spread over 4,610 sq ft carpet area in super-premium residential project Signature Island in 2015 for Rs 31.48 crore. The buyer has paid stamp duty of Rs 1.95 crore for the registration of the deal that took place on December 29.

news.title: Lenders fail to sell Evergrande's Hong Kong headquarters by tender: Sources
news.para: Lenders to the office tower, China Evergrande Centre, valued at between HK$8 billion and HK$9 billion ($1.02 billion and $1.15 billion), appointed a receiver in September to seize the asset and tender it for sale with a bid deadline of Oct 31.

news.title: China Evergrande's chairman says 2023 crucial for home delivery, debt repayment
news.para: Saddled with over $300 billion in liabilities and undergoing a debt restructuring, the world's most indebted property developer has been struggling to repay its many creditors and suppliers and complete projects.

news.title: UP-RERA website to improve services with launch of version 2.0 by May 2023
news.para: ​Packed with new-age technologies like artificial intelligence and machine learning, 'Version 2.0' portal will also help in reducing time and efforts in resolving complaints, speeding up actions against defaulters and ensuring ease of service at optimum level, UP RERA said in a statement.

news.title: South Korea eases property regulations across Seoul
news.para: Among 25 districts in Seoul, only four will remain on the finance ministry's "speculative area" list starting from Thursday, the ministry said. It currently consists of 15 districts.

news.title: Sebi returns OYO's draft IPO papers; asks to refile with updates
news.para: OYO filed preliminary documents with the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) in September 2021 for a Rs 8,430 crore IPO.
